Gulf Stocks: Drake & Scull International, National Investments

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-05-26T13:40:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/gulf-stocks-drake-scull-international-national-investments.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  advanced the
most since May 18, rising 0.5 percent at the 2 p.m. close in
Dubai and trimming its loss for the week to 3.1 percent. Abu
Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  dropped 0.1 percent and Saudi Arabia’s
market was closed for the weekend.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.        Drake & Scull International (DSI)   advanced the most in
more than two months, rising 3 percent to 1.03 dirhams. The
Dubai-based construction and engineering company said a fully
owned unit won contracts valued at 150 million dirhams ($41
million) in Europe,  China , the Middle East and North Africa.       National Investments Co. (NINV KK) snapped a three-day
drop, rising 0.9 percent to 238 fils. The Kuwaiti company
controlled by the Kharafi Group got approval for a six-month
extension to buy back 10 percent of shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  